    "body": "Would IPython.display.clear_output do the trick?\n\nOn Tue, Jan 7, 2014 at 7:15 AM, Thomas Wiecki notifications@github.comwrote:\n\n> (I posted this on the mailing list but it didn't receive replies).\n> \n> For a progress bar I am running multiple calls to display(Javascript(...)).\n> \n> This works fine but there are two problems:\n> 1. The state of the updated progress bar is not saved in the NB.\n> 2. Every call to display() adds a\n> to the cell's HTML. This causes a lot of white-space to appear.\n> \n> Essentially I want a way to change the cell's output inplace without\n> adding new output.\n> \n> Here is the code for reference (suggestions for improvement welcome):\n> \n> from IPython.core.display import HTML, Javascript, display\n> class ProgressBar(object):\n>     def **init**(self, iterations, animation_interval=.5):\n>         self.iterations = iterations\n>         self.start = time.time()\n>         self.last = 0\n>         self.animation_interval = animation_interval\n> \n> ```\n> def percentage(self, i):\n>     return 100 * i / float(self.iterations)\n> \n> def update(self, i):\n>     elapsed = time.time() - self.start\n>     i += 1\n> \n>     if elapsed - self.last > self.animation_interval:\n>         self.animate(i + 1, elapsed)\n>         self.last = elapsed\n>     elif i == self.iterations:\n>         self.animate(i, elapsed)\n> ```\n> \n> class IPythonNotebookPB(ProgressBar):\n>     def **init**(self, iterations):\n>         self.divid = str(uuid.uuid4())\n>         self.sec_id = str(uuid.uuid4())\n> \n> ```\n>     pb = HTML(\"\"\"<style media=\"screen\" type=\"text/css\">progress {  font-size: .6em;  line-height: 2em;  text-indent: .5em;  width: 60em;  height: 2em;}</style>\n> ```\n> \n> <progress id=\"%s\" max=\"100\"/><label id=\"%s\" text=\"Loading...\"/>\"\"\" % (self.divid, self.sec_id))\n>         display(pb)\n> \n> ```\n>     ProgressBar.__init__(self, iterations)\n> \n> def animate(self, i, elapsed):\n>     percentage = int(self.percentage(i))\n>     display(Javascript(\"document.getElementById('%s').value = %i;\" % (self.divid, percentage)))\n>     display(Javascript(\"$('label#%s').text('%i%% in %.1f sec')\" %\n>             (self.sec_id, percentage, round(elapsed, 1))))\n> ```\n> \n>  —\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHubhttps://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/4764\n> .\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
  },
